2mo i, 1:" 'Stolen!' he cried.
2mo i, 1:
2mo i, 1:" 'Yes, thief!' I roared, shaking him by the shoulder.
2mo i, 1:
2mo i, 1:" 'There are none missing. There cannot be any missing,' said he.
2mo i, 1:
2mo i, 1:" 'There are three missing. And you know where they are. Must I call you a liar as well as a thief? Did I not see you trying to tear off another piece?'
2mo i, 1:
2mo i, 1:" 'You have called me names enough,' said he, 'I will not stand it any longer. I shall not say another word about this business, since you have chosen to insult me. I will leave your house in the morning and make my own way in the world.'
